WEBVTT

00:12.360 --> 00:13.622
[Armstrong] Previously
onDead City...

00:14.144 --> 00:17.321
The man who's got Hershel,
they call him the Croat.

00:17.452 --> 00:20.194
-Who is worth following here?
-His name is Negan.

00:20.324 --> 00:21.804
[Negan] I knew that
he was a rabid dog

00:21.934 --> 00:23.719
that needed to be put down.

00:23.849 --> 00:25.808
Blew off his ear.
The rest of him got away.

00:25.938 --> 00:27.549
So he's gonna wanna kill you.

00:27.679 --> 00:28.898
[Tommaso] If you wanna
get to the Croat,

00:29.029 --> 00:30.421
you just gotta get
through that.

00:30.552 --> 00:32.075
[Maggie] He and the Croat
know each other.

00:32.206 --> 00:34.121
They go back.
He can bait him.

00:34.251 --> 00:36.036
Lure him out of the arena.

00:36.166 --> 00:36.993
Then we kill him.

00:54.315 --> 00:56.665
[bird squawking]

00:59.276 --> 01:01.017
[Negan] [hums to self]

01:06.370 --> 01:08.111
[door opens]

01:08.633 --> 01:10.157
[Simon] Hey, Neegs?

01:12.985 --> 01:14.161
[grunts]

01:16.467 --> 01:17.860
Um...

01:19.688 --> 01:21.037
We got a problem.

01:22.908 --> 01:25.041
[tense music]

01:25.172 --> 01:26.651
[grunts]

01:29.437 --> 01:39.447
[theme music]

02:15.439 --> 02:17.615
[Simon] I told him
to kibosh that shit.

02:17.746 --> 02:20.662
Said you gave the order, but you
know he don't listen to me.

02:20.792 --> 02:23.273
I mean, you know, I'm not
gonna say I told you so.

02:23.404 --> 02:24.927
I'm not that kind of guy, but

02:25.057 --> 02:26.624
certain folks, a lot of folks

02:26.755 --> 02:29.758
are saying it's time
to rein his ass in.

02:29.888 --> 02:33.892
Invest more authority in,
you know, someone not unlike...

02:37.113 --> 02:38.767
We did it.

02:38.897 --> 02:40.769
Negan, we did it.

02:40.899 --> 02:43.337
The girl, she confessed.

02:43.466 --> 02:46.296
She was sent by the King,
exactly like we--

02:46.427 --> 02:48.864
He said to let her walk!

02:48.994 --> 02:51.475
He gave a direct order.

02:51.606 --> 02:55.392
Negan, you know, these things...

02:55.523 --> 02:58.352
my process, it takes time.

02:58.482 --> 02:59.875
Your process?

03:00.005 --> 03:02.704
Yes, Simon, my process.

03:02.834 --> 03:04.836
Who determined the location
of the hidden arms cache

03:04.967 --> 03:06.098
at the Hilltop?

03:06.229 --> 03:07.709
[Simon] I would've
found that shit.

03:07.839 --> 03:09.928
[The Croat] Oh, really?
Your keen sense of observation.

03:10.059 --> 03:11.713
Your emotional intelligence.

03:11.843 --> 03:12.975
[Simon] Emoti-blah, blah, blah,

03:13.105 --> 03:14.629
this is what I'm
talking about, Negan.

03:14.759 --> 03:16.457
Usin' these highfalutin words

03:16.587 --> 03:21.636
to cover up what
we all know you really are.

03:21.766 --> 03:26.162
A Slavic, psychopathic nutjob.

03:26.293 --> 03:29.121
Oh my god, I refuse
to participate

03:29.252 --> 03:30.558
in these childish conversations.

03:30.688 --> 03:31.602
[Simon] Kids...

03:31.733 --> 03:33.561
KIDS

03:33.691 --> 03:37.956
is a line we do not cross.

03:38.609 --> 03:39.523
We all know that.

03:39.654 --> 03:41.351
Enough.

03:41.960 --> 03:47.009
Buraz, I know you understand.

03:50.491 --> 03:52.449
We had to be sure.

03:52.579 --> 03:58.499
[unsettling music]

04:12.600 --> 04:14.602
[Amaia] I looked everywhere.

04:15.777 --> 04:18.170
-What's that mean?
-It means I looked everywhere.

04:21.478 --> 04:22.914
So what? He took off?

04:23.045 --> 04:25.482
Passed him on my way
in last night.

04:25.613 --> 04:29.312
Anybody outside last night
maybe see Luther head out?

04:30.139 --> 04:31.793
Still no Luther?

04:31.923 --> 04:32.881
Where would he go?

04:33.011 --> 04:34.404
Not saying he went anywhere.

04:34.534 --> 04:36.885
Just... trying to figure it out.

04:37.015 --> 04:38.539
Well, it's a little hard
to picture a guy like that

04:38.669 --> 04:40.018
playing hide-and-seek.

04:40.149 --> 04:43.761
All I know is he wasn't
real keen on this plan.

04:43.892 --> 04:46.460
[Tommaso] Yeah, it's true.
He didn't want no part in this.

04:48.157 --> 04:50.115
How long we gonna wait?

04:50.246 --> 04:51.508
Every hour's more time
for the psycho

04:51.639 --> 04:53.075
to figure out we're comin'.

04:54.772 --> 04:58.254
Hey, hey, come on.
Luther's his own guy, right?

04:58.385 --> 05:00.300
He can do what he wants.

05:00.430 --> 05:01.997
Tell you what.

05:02.127 --> 05:04.695
Time he gets back and
sees the shit we pulled,

05:04.826 --> 05:07.350
his thankful ass gonna be
kissin' your butt ugly feet.

05:07.481 --> 05:10.353
[Amaia]
[laughs] Oh yeah?

05:12.703 --> 05:14.314
[Tommaso] We're good.

05:16.316 --> 05:17.404
[Amaia] 'Kay.

05:19.188 --> 05:20.885
[Negan grunts]

05:27.022 --> 05:28.589
[grunts in pain]

05:30.199 --> 05:31.548
[sighs]

05:32.984 --> 05:37.075
Nah, it's cool.
It's, uh... it's gettin' better.

05:37.206 --> 05:41.732
[harmonica playing]

05:51.742 --> 05:53.788
-You ready?
-Yeah.

05:58.575 --> 06:01.273
You know what?
Honestly...

06:01.404 --> 06:05.016
No, I'm not.

06:05.147 --> 06:07.497
And no, it's not
'cause he wants me dead.

06:07.628 --> 06:11.762
Hell, lots of people
have wanted me dead.

06:11.893 --> 06:14.461
It's hard to explain,
you know? It's...

06:14.591 --> 06:17.986
The closer
we get to the Croat...

06:18.116 --> 06:20.597
it just starts to feel
a bit too goddamn familiar.

06:20.728 --> 06:23.121
Like, if he starts talkin',
it won't be him at all.

06:23.252 --> 06:24.819
It's gonna be the
echo of some song

06:24.949 --> 06:26.603
that I don't wanna hear no more.

06:26.734 --> 06:31.347
[harmonica starts up again]

06:32.566 --> 06:34.263
What is it?

06:36.744 --> 06:39.659
When Hershel was a baby,

06:39.790 --> 06:41.052
like four or five months old,

06:41.183 --> 06:44.273
there was this guy,
Amos, living above us.

06:44.404 --> 06:47.276
And Hershel was having
trouble sleeping, and...

06:47.407 --> 06:51.498
Amos decided it was a good
time to learn the harmonica.

06:51.628 --> 06:55.371
I asked him very nicely if he
could stop practicing at night.

06:55.502 --> 06:58.635
And, uh, he said that he would.

07:00.332 --> 07:02.030
Come that night,
he did it again.

07:03.553 --> 07:05.163
So the next time he was
out on a hunting expedition,

07:05.294 --> 07:06.730
I snuck into his room
and I stole the harmonica,

07:06.861 --> 07:08.645
and I went and buried it
in the fucking ground.

07:12.344 --> 07:14.782
Well...

07:14.912 --> 07:17.524
I bet you lost a couple
Girl Scout badges for that.

07:20.962 --> 07:22.920
Yeah, but I'm sure you would've
buried it somewhere way worse.

07:23.051 --> 07:24.705
[Negan chuckles]

07:28.491 --> 07:30.188
Have you, uh...

07:30.319 --> 07:33.061
You seen my matches?

07:33.191 --> 07:34.541
No.

07:40.198 --> 07:46.074
[foreboding music]

07:56.954 --> 08:02.743
[walkers growling]

08:18.454 --> 08:24.460
[bubbling]

08:27.768 --> 08:30.422
[Tommaso] It's methane.

08:30.553 --> 08:32.467
From the sewers.

08:49.529 --> 08:55.447
[tense, eerie music]

09:03.847 --> 09:09.287
[walker growling]

09:15.729 --> 09:21.517
[music intensifies]

09:23.780 --> 09:29.525
[walker growling]

09:35.705 --> 09:40.841
[walker growling]

09:43.191 --> 09:50.981
[music continues]

10:15.919 --> 10:21.882
[walkers growling]

10:24.493 --> 10:31.543
