31:45.686 --> 31:47.557
Negan!

31:47.688 --> 31:50.212
[laughs]

31:50.343 --> 31:52.954
My brother!

31:53.085 --> 31:56.088
Buraz!

31:56.218 --> 32:00.744
Oh, I see you have
their weapon of choice.

32:04.313 --> 32:05.880
Truce.

32:07.273 --> 32:08.665
No?

32:12.713 --> 32:14.149
[sighs]

32:15.585 --> 32:17.848
You know...

32:19.024 --> 32:20.982
I heard what happened
at that bank.

32:23.767 --> 32:27.293
It sounded like your handiwork.

32:27.423 --> 32:30.383
You assumed I wanted revenge.

32:30.513 --> 32:33.212
Tit for tat.

32:33.342 --> 32:37.564
So you found common cause
with your new friends.

32:37.694 --> 32:38.957
You blew off my ear!

32:39.087 --> 32:41.350
So what? I have another!

32:48.444 --> 32:51.882
Where is Lucille?

32:52.013 --> 32:53.580
She's gone.

32:53.710 --> 32:55.451
She broken?

32:57.366 --> 32:59.673
One too many hits
to the heads, eh?

32:59.803 --> 33:01.762
[chuckles]

33:02.719 --> 33:05.679
No, I...

33:05.809 --> 33:09.465
I understand.

33:09.596 --> 33:12.164
I saw Jerome on the mainland.

33:12.294 --> 33:15.384
He told me about the
war with the Hilltop,

33:15.515 --> 33:17.778
the Kingdom...

33:17.908 --> 33:20.737
Alexandria.

33:20.868 --> 33:23.958
I should have been there.

33:24.089 --> 33:27.657
I can only imagine
the damage Simon caused.

33:29.050 --> 33:30.965
He never listened...

33:31.096 --> 33:34.490
never really listened to you.

33:35.665 --> 33:37.667
It's okay.

33:37.798 --> 33:41.193
It's okay you lost
the Sanctuary,

33:41.323 --> 33:46.807
'cause I have built a new one.

33:46.937 --> 33:49.288
And we'll keep going.

33:49.418 --> 33:51.420
We'll build something
bigger, stronger!

33:51.551 --> 33:56.034
The whole island will
become our sanctuary,

33:56.164 --> 33:59.341
fueled by the death
in its bowels.

34:01.648 --> 34:03.258
Okay!

34:04.825 --> 34:07.480
Business first, then pleasure.

34:07.610 --> 34:10.831
I know who you want.

34:10.960 --> 34:13.572
He's here with me, right now.

34:13.703 --> 34:15.096
Let me see him.

34:15.226 --> 34:16.967
Of course!

34:17.098 --> 34:18.752
Yes, yes, of course.

34:18.882 --> 34:25.063
[unsettling music]

34:34.811 --> 34:37.987
You recognize him, no?

34:38.119 --> 34:40.947
[chuckles] He's the marshal

34:41.079 --> 34:45.083
who has been pursuing
you so doggedly.

34:45.213 --> 34:48.347
I am here for the kid. Hershel.

34:48.476 --> 34:51.219
[The Croat] Yes, that's right,
the marshal told me.

34:51.350 --> 34:52.568
He told me.

34:52.699 --> 34:54.266
So...

34:55.266 --> 34:57.486
You're still helping the widow.

34:59.923 --> 35:01.273
What did she promise you?

35:01.403 --> 35:02.839
[laughs]

35:02.970 --> 35:06.278
What will you get for him?

35:06.408 --> 35:09.455
Just... give me the kid.

35:09.585 --> 35:11.761
This will be difficult.

35:14.286 --> 35:17.332
This will require
a conversation.

35:17.463 --> 35:19.378
[chuckles]

35:20.118 --> 35:21.206
Come to me.

35:21.336 --> 35:22.903
Come, come, come, come.

35:23.033 --> 35:25.340
Come, we'll discuss.

35:27.777 --> 35:29.518
You don't trust me yet.

35:29.649 --> 35:32.304
I understand.

35:32.434 --> 35:35.350
I will make a gesture

35:35.481 --> 35:40.921
to show you that I come only
in the spirit of friendship...

35:43.358 --> 35:44.794
and brotherly love.

35:52.411 --> 35:53.847
[screams]

35:53.977 --> 35:58.982
[grunting]

36:00.984 --> 36:05.119
[grunting]

36:05.250 --> 36:07.382
[The Croat] Negan,
what are you doing?

36:07.513 --> 36:10.429
[grunting]

36:14.520 --> 36:15.695
Aah!

36:15.825 --> 36:19.394
[grunting]

36:21.135 --> 36:22.484
Go, go!

36:24.356 --> 36:30.275
[grunting]

36:31.580 --> 36:36.672
[tense, pulsating music]

36:36.803 --> 36:38.587
Aah!

36:39.545 --> 36:41.199
[grunting]

36:43.679 --> 36:46.247
[grunting]

36:47.727 --> 36:51.426
[music continues]

36:53.863 --> 36:56.692
[Armstrong pants]

37:00.218 --> 37:02.437
[grunting]

37:02.568 --> 37:03.873
It's too heavy!

37:04.004 --> 37:05.092
No, we can do it, go!

37:05.223 --> 37:06.528
Push together. Go!

37:06.659 --> 37:10.619
[grunting]
[metallic scraping]

37:15.755 --> 37:17.235
It's good, it's good.
It's good.

37:17.365 --> 37:21.543
[panting]

37:24.329 --> 37:27.462
[walkers growling]
[banging]

37:32.075 --> 37:33.207
The sewers.

37:33.338 --> 37:34.121
We can get out
through the sewers.

37:34.252 --> 37:36.036
Let's go!

37:38.081 --> 37:40.214
[grunting]

37:40.345 --> 37:41.476
What's this?

37:43.522 --> 37:46.829
[walkers growling]
[banging]

37:48.875 --> 37:51.660
I told you, it's too dangerous.

37:51.791 --> 37:53.575
All the dead are down there,
and the air, we can't breathe--

37:53.706 --> 37:55.534
Amaia, what other
options we got?

37:55.664 --> 37:57.144
We got to.

37:57.275 --> 38:00.756
[walkers growling]

38:00.887 --> 38:02.541
Come on.

38:05.152 --> 38:09.591
[crickets chirping]

38:12.638 --> 38:15.771
[grunting]

38:22.691 --> 38:24.737
[crickets chirping]

38:25.651 --> 38:27.479
All right, man...

38:27.609 --> 38:29.263
I think we bought ourselves
a little bit of time,

38:29.394 --> 38:30.612
to figure out what the hell--

38:30.743 --> 38:33.702
Code 14, Section 2.

38:33.833 --> 38:36.792
Intentional killing shall be
defined as first degree murder

38:36.923 --> 38:40.622
and shall be punishable by
supplementary execution.

38:40.753 --> 38:43.756
Times five.

38:43.886 --> 38:45.888
You're a dick.

38:46.019 --> 38:53.331
[unsettling music]

38:53.461 --> 38:57.465
[walkers growling]
[banging]

38:59.293 --> 39:04.385
[music continues]

39:19.487 --> 39:21.489
Let's go.

39:21.620 --> 39:27.452
[walkers growling]
[banging]

39:31.717 --> 39:37.505
[music continues]

39:39.159 --> 39:43.424
[walkers growling]
[banging]

39:54.479 --> 39:57.307
[sigh]

39:57.438 --> 40:01.268
[metallic scraping]

40:01.399 --> 40:05.620
[grunting]

40:09.537 --> 40:12.758
[pants]

40:12.888 --> 40:15.978
[walkers growling]
[banging]

40:22.463 --> 40:24.987
[music intensifying]

40:25.118 --> 40:28.251
[creaking]

40:29.252 --> 40:32.168
[walkers growling]

40:36.172 --> 40:37.652
Woman: I just can't
figure it out.

40:37.783 --> 40:39.306
The Burazi.

40:39.437 --> 40:40.612
They knew.

40:40.742 --> 40:43.310
Anyone see what happened
to Negan?

40:43.441 --> 40:46.313
He's got the whole island
locked down.

40:46.444 --> 40:47.706
Where is he?

40:47.836 --> 40:49.751
The Croat: I will find him.

40:49.882 --> 40:51.884
♪

40:52.014 --> 40:53.581
[Walker growls]
[Perlie grunts]

40:54.930 --> 40:57.455
There is no way
they're getting off this island.

40:57.585 --> 40:58.978
[Walker growling]

40:59.108 --> 41:01.807
[Monster roaring]

41:07.116 --> 41:09.597
I'm Eli Jorné, EP
and showrunner of "Dead City,"

41:09.728 --> 41:13.819
and this is episode four,
"Everybody Wins a Prize."

41:13.949 --> 41:16.517
You get your kid.
We kill the psycho.

41:16.648 --> 41:17.866
Everybody wins a prize.

41:17.997 --> 41:19.781
I like that as a title
for the episode

41:19.912 --> 41:23.611
because there's a kind of,
like, tragic irony to it.

41:23.742 --> 41:25.657
As soon as I decided
that The Croat was going to be

41:25.787 --> 41:27.572
holed up in this arena,
I was like,

41:27.702 --> 41:29.356
Well, we got to fill it up
with walkers, obviously,

41:29.487 --> 41:31.358
and there has to be
a giant battle.

41:31.489 --> 41:33.012
I was excited
for that whole sequence.

41:33.142 --> 41:38.104
I knew it was going to be epic
and I'm so blown away.

41:38.234 --> 41:41.063
The director, Kevin Dowling,
just did an incredible job.

41:41.194 --> 41:42.848
Everybody involved
did such a great job.

41:42.978 --> 41:45.720
And I think he did it in
like just a couple of days.

41:45.851 --> 41:48.027
So many shots,
so much you got to cover.

41:48.157 --> 41:52.118
[Walkers growling]

41:52.248 --> 41:54.860
It's not just about seeing
the violence and the fighting.

41:54.990 --> 41:56.688
It's also about catching those
really important

41:56.818 --> 41:58.690
emotional moments of,
you know, when Tommaso and Amaia

41:58.820 --> 42:00.735
see each other
across the arena

42:00.866 --> 42:03.695
and you see, you know,
the love in their eyes,

42:03.825 --> 42:06.175
the longing, the fear,
and you realize,

42:06.306 --> 42:07.699
like, these people have so much

42:07.829 --> 42:09.657
to lose as they watch
each other, you know,

42:09.788 --> 42:12.138
get swallowed up
by mobs of walkers.

42:12.268 --> 42:14.227
No!

42:14.357 --> 42:16.577
So there's this crucial moment
where Maggie,

42:16.708 --> 42:18.274
she sees a way out

42:18.405 --> 42:20.494
and then she stops
with this sort of sixth sense,

42:20.625 --> 42:23.671
and she turns, and there's
Ginny inside the octagon,

42:23.802 --> 42:25.325
safe but trapped,

42:25.455 --> 42:27.066
and she has a moment
there where she has to decide,

42:27.196 --> 42:28.633
am I going to keep going
or am I going to turn back?

42:28.763 --> 42:30.635
And I like to think
of that moment

42:30.765 --> 42:32.071
as connected
to this earlier moment

42:32.201 --> 42:35.857
when Maggie finds
the tin of beeswax.

42:35.988 --> 42:38.164
♪

42:38.294 --> 42:41.733
Don't act like you never did
something you needed to explain.

42:41.863 --> 42:44.039
He basically says,
"We're not that different.

42:44.170 --> 42:45.824
Don't pretend
that you're better than me."

42:45.954 --> 42:48.304
I think, on some level,
it's a combination for her of

42:48.435 --> 42:50.306
when she's staring
at that little girl,

42:50.437 --> 42:52.004
she can't leave her behind,

42:52.134 --> 42:54.702
but also her needing to not be
the person that Negan is,

42:54.833 --> 42:57.444
to not be at his level,
to be better than that.

42:57.575 --> 42:59.533
So episode four opens
with a flashback

42:59.664 --> 43:01.361
of Negan and The Croat.

43:01.491 --> 43:03.668
Hopefully everybody gets a kick
out of seeing Simon again.

43:03.798 --> 43:05.017
I sure did.

43:05.147 --> 43:07.976
Um...

43:08.107 --> 43:09.543
We got a problem.

43:09.674 --> 43:11.806
When the actor Steven Ogg
showed up,

43:11.937 --> 43:13.721
he and Jeffrey
were, like, cracking jokes

43:13.852 --> 43:16.724
and having the time of their
lives like two little kids.

43:16.855 --> 43:19.466
And it's a scene where we really
get to see that experience

43:19.597 --> 43:21.337
of what that felt like for Negan
to walk into this room

43:21.468 --> 43:23.905
and see this young girl
the same age as Ginny,

43:24.036 --> 43:25.515
maybe, that The Croat
has tortured to death,

43:25.646 --> 43:28.431
and he doesn't even see
what he's done.

43:28.562 --> 43:31.652
And it's really hard and painful
for Negan to witness.

43:31.783 --> 43:33.523
And then, we kind of
come out in the present

43:33.654 --> 43:35.613
and we realize this isn't
just a generic flashback.

43:35.743 --> 43:37.223
This is what's on Negan's mind.

43:37.353 --> 43:40.574
The closer we get
to The Croat,

43:40.705 --> 43:42.881
it just starts to feel a bit too
[no audio] damn familiar.

43:43.011 --> 43:45.492
I know it maybe sounds odd
to say, thinking of the fact

43:45.623 --> 43:47.059
that The Croat
is probably older than Negan,

43:47.189 --> 43:50.105
but in some ways, The Croat
was his first child.

43:50.236 --> 43:52.194
He taught him how to bounce back

43:52.325 --> 43:54.980
from the tragedy
of the loss of his family

43:55.110 --> 43:57.852
and how to survive
in this threatening world.

43:57.983 --> 43:59.593
[Cocks gun]

43:59.724 --> 44:02.422
Negan!

44:02.552 --> 44:04.511
[Laughs]

44:04.642 --> 44:06.339
My brother!

44:06.469 --> 44:08.950
The Croat is so excited
to see Negan,

44:09.081 --> 44:10.691
and he kind of wants
to show off this world

44:10.822 --> 44:12.824
that he's built, you know,
in a kind of like,

44:12.954 --> 44:14.695
"Look, Dad,
look what you showed me

44:14.826 --> 44:15.957
and look what I built."

44:16.088 --> 44:19.961
I have built a new world.

44:20.092 --> 44:24.618
The whole island
will become our Sanctuary.

44:24.749 --> 44:27.839
I think the most fun thing
to watch as a producer on set

44:27.969 --> 44:32.104
was when they threw Armstrong
over the edge of the catwalk.

44:32.234 --> 44:35.411
Aah! Aah!

44:35.542 --> 44:38.110
Jorné: Oh, man, that catwalk,
that was scary.

44:38.240 --> 44:39.851
I have a terrible fear
of heights.

44:39.981 --> 44:43.071
And in pre-production,
we went to go,

44:43.202 --> 44:46.640
you know, like scout
the catwalk above the arena.

44:46.771 --> 44:48.686
Even before we were
like out on the catwalk,

44:48.816 --> 44:50.905
I just started shaking
and I couldn't move.

44:51.036 --> 44:52.341
And I had to stop
and turn around

44:52.472 --> 44:54.039
and I never went up there again.

44:54.169 --> 44:55.388
[Negan grunting]

44:55.518 --> 44:57.738
The Croat: Negan,
what are you doing?

44:57.869 --> 44:59.392
[Grunting]

44:59.522 --> 45:01.655
Jorné: The moment where Negan
saves Armstrong's life

45:01.786 --> 45:03.396
was something that I always knew
was going to happen.

45:03.526 --> 45:07.269
And that was inspired by
the story from "Les Misérables."

45:07.400 --> 45:09.271
But I think that's a big moment
for Armstrong

45:09.402 --> 45:13.972
that the man who he's been
chasing down to hang him

45:14.102 --> 45:16.191
just saved his life.

45:16.322 --> 45:23.416
♪

45:24.722 --> 45:34.732
[outro music]
